cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use FEMP-X, please cite the dataset release below.
type: dataset
title: "FEMP-X: A Witness-Augmented Dataset for Candidate Functionally Equivalent Java Method Pairs"
authors:
  - family-names: Higo
    given-names: Yoshiki
    affiliation: "The University of Osaka"
repository-code: "https://github.com/YoshikiHigo/FEMP-X"
url: "https://github.com/YoshikiHigo/FEMP-X"
abstract: >-
  FEMP-X is a witness-augmented dataset for candidate functionally equivalent
  Java method pairs. It extends an original candidate pool of 13,710 Java
  method pairs with execution-validated witnesses of inequivalence generated in
  a Codex-based workflow using GPT-5.4. The release is designed to support
  research on semantic clone detection, behavioral similarity analysis,
  counterexample generation, executable test generation, and LLM-assisted
  dataset curation.
keywords:
  - dataset
  - code clone
  - semantic clone detection
  - functionally equivalent methods
  - counterexample generation
  - behavioral similarity
  - Java
license: "CC-BY-NC 4.0"

version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-04-13"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.19543614"
